Uses of CoordinateSystem in com.esri.mo2.cs.geod
 

Subinterfaces of CoordinateSystem in com.esri.mo2.cs.geod
 interface Projection
          represents a geodetic projection that transforms coordinates to and from geographic coordinates.
 interface ReferencedCoordinateSystem
          Represents a coordinate system geo-referenced to WGS84 by datum transformation, thus a point in any ReferencedCoordinateSystem can be transformed to any other ReferencedCoordinateSystem.

 class EquidistantConic
          Implements a EquidistantConic projection for an ellipsoid: Conic Equidistant Neither conformal nor equal-area Parallels are arcs of concentric circles at true spacing Meridians are equally spaced radii of the same circles, intersecting parallels at right angles Scale is true along meridians and along 1 or 2 standard parallels Developed by Ptolemy in 150 AD Used for maps of small countries and for maps of larger areas with east west expanse.
